results.raw: Search for Burglary Suspect Who Fatally Shot Dog at 2000 Margaret St, Saint Paul, Minnesota, 55119
results.rawLocation: 2000 Margaret St, Saint Paul, Minnesota, 55119
results.title: Search for Burglary Suspect Who Fatally Shot Dog

-Mski294qGwou6mQlsCw.text: Police are attempting to identify a suspect they say used a shovel to break into a home, steal a gun, and shoot a Golden Retriever on his way out Wednesday morning at 9:45 a.m.

nib.text:
Police are seeking to identify a man they say fatally shot a family dog after breaking into an East Side home Wednesday morning.

It happened at about 9:45 a.m. on the 2000 block of Margaret Street in Conway, according to the Saint Paul Police Department.

Police said the suspect broke into the home with a shovel, stole a gun and other items, and shot and killed a Golden Retriever on his way out.

He is described as a Black man with tattoos on his right cheek and hands and was last seen wearing blue jeans, a black hooded sweatshirt with red lettering on the front, black and white shoes, and a black Chicago Blackhawks cap with a red brim.

Anyone who recognized the suspect is urged to call SPPD at 651-266-5867.

nib.text:
A man was arrested after stealing a vehicle with a 3-month old baby inside Thursday morning in Prospect Park, officials said.

In the 3300 block of University Avenue, a woman left her vehicle running at a convenience store at approximately 11:11 a.m.

An unknown man jumped into the vehicle and took off with the woman's baby still inside, fleeing westbound on University Avenue SE.

In under 10 minutes, responding officers located the vehicle two blocks away with the unharmed child inside, MPD officials told [CBS Minnesota](https://minnesota.cbslocal.com/2022/01/06/mpd-suspect-arrested-after-stealing-running-vehicle-with-3-month-old-inside/).

The suspect, who fled from the scene, was later found and arrested by officers.
